member.name: T:tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token
member.summary: The base token for all of dylan.NET.
member.remarks: Any token should inherit from this class if it to be considered a token.

member.name: C:tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token
member.remarks: Please do implement a new constructor for new tokens (should inherit this) if they have new fields. The dylan.NET code mostly uses this constructor and not the other one.

member.name: C:tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token(System.String)
member.param: The string variable to be assigned to the 'Value' field of the token.
member.summary: Constructs the Token object while assigning the given param to 'Value'.
member.remarks: Use this as a shortcut when manually porting a token into a class that inherits Token. Normally this constructor is not used so much evn though it is supported like the other one. Please do implement a new constructor for new tokens (should inherit this) if they have new fields. Implement both constructors in such cases.

member.name: F:tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token.Line
member.summary: The line number the token is found in. This helps debug file making and is really important.
member.remarks: Please do not forget to assign the value of 'Line' to the 'Line' of the target inheritor of 'Token' while porting to another object inheriting 'Token'.
